What AI Was NOT Used For
To be explicit, the following were not AI generated:

- The research question itself. The framing of insider trading detection as a data science problem, and the specific focus on alpha as the central metric, were my own.
- Hypothesis formulation. The four hypotheses tested were proposed by me.
- Methodological choices. The decision to use Welch's t- est over a standard t test, to exclude alpha from the Random Forest feature set, to set a 5% alpha threshold for the suspicious label and to include the 90 day horizon alongside the 30 day window all of these were my choices.
- Interpretation of results. Every conclusion drawn from the statistical output was my interpretation, not the AI's.
- Critical reading of AI output. In several cases, notably the report drafting, I explicitly rejected AI output because it misrepresented the data.
- The sector ticker map. The mapping of 33 specific tickers to their respective sectors (Technology, Healthcare, Finance, Energy, Defense) used in the feature engineering pipeline was compiled by me and passed to the AI as a specification.

Generally all the ideas that later applied as a code was my ideas. 


